JOHANNESBURG – Fairfax Africa Investments has pulled out of the bid to buy a stake in PPC Cement. This comes after PPC’s board rejected Fairfaix’s partial offer last month. The Canadian investment firm had offered the cement maker about R2-billion for a 23 percent stake in the company. READ: Ireland's CRH joins battle for PPC cement Had it been approved by shareholders, the deal would have led to a merger between PPC and its rival cement maker AfriSam. Dublin-based CRH and Nigerian cement producer Dangote previously pulled out of the bidding war. This now leaves Swiss building materials group LafargeHolcim as PPC’s sole remaining bidder. eNCA